comments: Jerome (OKC) and Fournier (BOS) make incidental foot to foot contact out on the perimeter.
Thompson (BOS) jumps alongside Roby (OKC) to contest his driving shot attempt and any body contact is deemed marginal.
Thompson (BOS) jumps alongside and absorbs the contact created by Jerome (OKC) during his driving shot attempt.
Thompson (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Jerome's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact.

Smart (BOS) reaches for the ball and avoids any contact with Bazley's (OKC) arm, when he dribbles the ball off of his own knee on the spin move. Any contact as Brown (BOS) and Bazley (OKC) dive to the floor as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Jerome (OKC) makes contact with Smart (BOS) as he gathers the ball and affects his driving shot attempt.
Fournier (BOS) extends his arm to try and deflect the pass and any contact with Bazley's (OKC) hand is deemed incidental.
Langford (BOS) avoids making contact to Bazley's (OKC) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) jumps into and makes contact with Pritchard's (BOS) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes contact to Maledon's (OKC) arm and the contact affects his SQBR.
Dort (OKC) jumps into and makes contact with Brown's (BOS) body, which affects his play at the basket.
Langford (BOS) makes marginal contact to Bazley (OKC) after he already releases the pass on the take-foul attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes clean ball contact to tie the rebound up with Maledon (OKC) and a jump ball is correctly whistled.
Pritchard (BOS) commits a take foul on Dort (OKC).
Fournier (BOS) has his arm wrapped around Bazley's (OKC) back, and the contact affects his FOM and ability to get the pass.
After the steal, Bazley (OKC) makes contact to Fournier's (BOS) arm and the contact affects his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul on Roby (OKC).
Dort (OKC) legally contests Brown's (BOS) half court shot attempt and incidental contact occurs after Brown loses his balance and stumbles into Dort.
